    Replace aiomqtt with paho-mqtt threaded loop
    
    aiomqtt internally calls add_reader/add_writer on the asyncio event loop,
    which raises NotImplementedError on Windows where qasync wraps
    ProactorEventLoop. Replace with paho-mqtt's own loop_start/loop_stop
    background thread which has no interaction with asyncio's socket layer.
    
    MqttDriver.connect() uses asyncio.to_thread for the blocking connect/wait,
    set_state() calls paho.publish() directly (thread-safe, non-blocking).
    Connection failure at startup logs a warning and marks the output inactive
    instead of crashing the app.
    
    Co-Authored-By: Claude Sonnet 4.6 <noreply@anthropic.com>

